Georgia debuted in the first edition of the North Vision Song Contest. The country has never reached the top 10, with their best result in the contest being two twelfth-place finishes; achieved by Cici Manulashvili with the song "Unarmed" (#20), and Cira with "Hun Bun" (#23). Having failed to qualify in their first eleven attempts, Georgia qualified for the final for the first time in its history during the fourteenth edition with Rati Durglishvili's "Paper Boat". One edition later, Nina Sublatti became the second Georgian entrant to reach the final, placing twenty-second in the fifteenth edition. Georgia then failed to qualify to the final in five out of six editions between #16 and #21, before withdrawing from the contest in the twenty-second edition. Since their return for the twenty-third edition, Georgia have become more successful, qualifying for the final in five out of eight contests.

OGAN Second Chance Contest[]

The contest takes place during the contest, usually during the second semi-final of the respective edition. It is not a televised event, but only on YouTube. Georgia debuted in the third edition, held for the tenth edition.

Junior North Vision Song Contest[]

The contest is only for European artists under the age of 16. Georgia debuted in the third edition.
